{"schema_version":"1","crate":"wikiada","version":"1.5.0","id":"5b76b46b8283859a","name":"Wiki.Filters.Variables","qualified_name":"Wiki.Filters.Variables","kind":"ada_package","location":{"file":"src/wiki-filters-variables.ads","line":26,"column":9},"code":"package Wiki.Filters.Variables","documentation":{"description":"=== Variables Filters ===\nThe `Wiki.Filters.Variables` package defines a filter that replaces variables\nin the text, links, quotes.  Variables are represented as `$name`, `$(name)`\nor `${name}`.  When a variable is not found, the original string is not modified.\nThe list of variables is either configured programatically through the\n`Add_Variable` procedures but it can also be set from the Wiki text by using\nthe `Wiki.Plugins.Variables` plugin.\n\nThe variable filter must be configured with the plugin by declaring the instance:\n\n  F : aliased Wiki.Filters.Html.Html_Filter_Type;\n\n   Engine.Add_Filter (F'Unchecked_Access);\n\nAnd variables can be inserted by using the `Add_Variable` procedure:\n\n  F.Add_Variable (\"username\", \"gandalf\");"},"tagged_types":[{"id":"151691bfadd7d22b","name":"Variable_Filter","qualified_name":"Wiki.Filters.Variables.Variable_Filter","kind":"ada_tagged_type","location":{"file":"src/wiki-filters-variables.ads","line":28,"column":9},"code":"type Variable_Filter is new Filter_Type with private;","parent_type":{"qualified_name":"Wiki.Filters.Filter_Type","id":"0476abf5ee3ebe72","unit":"wiki-filters"},"dispatching_declared":[{"qualified_name":"Wiki.Filters.Variables.Add_Variable","id":"ec02bf58613eeb7c","unit":"wiki-filters-variables"},{"qualified_name":"Wiki.Filters.Variables.Add_Variable","id":"b18941927556a23d","unit":"wiki-filters-variables"},{"qualified_name":"Wiki.Filters.Variables.Expand","id":"ae6babd08a5e2aeb","unit":"wiki-filters-variables"},{"qualified_name":"Wiki.Filters.Variables.Iterate","id":"082a1fb2d9a54b36","unit":"wiki-filters-variables"}],"dispatching_overridden":[{"qualified_name":"Wiki.Filters.